Red's voice drops to something older than poetry:

'Forget the manuscript. That's not how you survive this night.

'Soho takes things from people — books, money, years. But she gives something back to those who listen. Three lines of an aubade, scattered through the dark. Find them before dawn and you'll walk out of here whole.

'Miss them, and you'll be just another ghost on Dean Street.'

He presses something cold into your palm. When you look down, there's nothing there — only words burning in your mind:

