:: Morris's Office {"position":"2750,650","size":"100,100"}
You find the building on Frith Street, on the door: M. Morris.

You knock.

'Come in. You must.'

You do.

He lifts the needle from his record, sinks his glass then tops it up (it's scotch and soda), then turns to his desk with his elbows and settling them individually, says, 'You were sent by Jeffrey?'

You nod.

'Well give it over.'

You put the manusicrip on the scuffed leather deasktop.

He reads the first page. Then the last page. Then a page from the middle.

(if: $confidence >= 60)[
He sets it down, carefully, as one might set a toffler on the floor.

'This itsn't bad. Have you got a job? A wife? Children? How long can you give to me? You've something but there's work to do. Lot's of work.'

This is as close as you've ever been.

