:: No more [End] {"position":"1400,550","size":"100,100"}
Centre Point is still behind you. It's been there all day long.

The way that you conceive, now, of its height is more temporal than spacial and like time but not but like space it remains impossible, merely notional; has a quality that space only attains when we imagine it infinitely.

One jumping from the top should fall forever and seem to fall as a ton of feathers falls in a perfect vacuum.

Standing here you can see London, Carthage, Liverpool and everything else.

